# SPA fallback for client-side routing.
#
# Why this exists
# ---------------
# When a user hits a deep URL (e.g. /event-guidelines, /vn/host-guide) we want
# the host to serve the pre-rendered HTML for that route if it exists, and
# otherwise fall through to index.html so React Router can handle it.
#
# Cloudflare Pages honors a `_redirects` file. Pre-rendered routes ship real
# HTML at /event-guidelines/index.html, /vn/index.html, etc., so those are
# served directly — this catch-all only kicks in for routes the crawler-facing
# prerender didn't cover (mostly fat-finger URLs).

